annotationA: Ubiquitin-60S ribosomal protein L40; Ubiquitin: exists either covalently attached to another protein, or free (unanchored). When covalently bound, it is conjugated to target proteins via an isopeptide bond either as a monomer (monoubiquitin), a polymer linked via different Lys residues of the ubiquitin (polyubiquitin chains) or a linear polymer linked via the initiator Met of the ubiquitin (linear polyubiquitin chains). annotationB: Espinas (Esn) is a LIM domain protein that binds to the seven-pass transmembrane cadherin stan. This stan-Esn interplay elicits repulsion between dendritic branches of Drosophila sensory neurons; Belongs to the prickle / espinas / testin family
